设 $\mathrm{n}=\mathrm{a}_{k} \mathrm{p}^{k}+a_{k-1} p^{k-1}+\cdots+\mathrm{a}_{0}, \mathrm{a}_{i} \in\{0,1, \cdots, \mathrm{p}-1\}$

则 $\operatorname{Ord}_{p}(\mathrm{n} !)=\sum_{i=1}^{+\infty}\left[\frac{n}{p^{i}}\right]$

$$
\begin{aligned}
& =a_{k} p^{k-1}+a_{k-1} p^{k-2}+\cdots+a_{2} p+a_{1} \\
& +a_{k} p^{k-2}+a_{k-1} p^{k-3}+\cdots+a_{2} \\
& +\cdots+a_{k}
\end{aligned}
$$

$$
\begin{aligned}
& =a_{k} \frac{p^{k}-1}{p-1}+a_{k-1} \frac{p^{k-1}-1}{p-1}+\cdots+a_{2} \frac{p^{2}-1}{p-1}+a_{1} \frac{p^{1}-1}{p-1} \\
& =\frac{\left(a_{k} p^{k}+a_{k-1} p^{k-1}+\cdots a_{1} p+a_{0}\right)-\left(a_{k}+a_{k-1}+\cdots a_{1}+a_{0}\right)}{p-1} \\
& =\frac{n-S_{P}(n)}{P-1}
\end{aligned}
$$

